summary:
I am a master's graduate interested in working for an organization that focuses on English education and/or human rights issues. Working in some form of social work, I intend to use my acquired knowledge to develop skills that can expand my expertise within the field.

Currently, I am working as a freelancing teacher of English as a Second Language (ZZP) and am extensively involved in volunteering. Through teaching, I can focus more on my field of study: human rights, education, English as a Second Language, workers rights, human trafficking, refugees, immigration and/or social work. Many of my students come from various socioeconomic and educative backgrounds. It is an opportunity for me to use my experiences to help my students address their needs and meet their goals. 

Furthermore, I am the Course Adviser/ESL Coordinator at the English Center. This small institution, located in Amsterdam and Amstelveen, focuses on personal training and enhancing communication skills in the English language. Providing private one-on-one lessons, this organization allows me to venture more into the academic world and pursue a teaching career.

In addition to my supervisor position, I am also volunteering at a small non-profit organization called de Regenboog Groep. This organization assists numerous individuals in various vulnerable positions, such as human trafficking, homelessness, and alcoholism. De Regenboog Groep introduced me to many individuals experiencing exploitation and discrimination. As a volunteer, I am directly involved with clients who encountered cases of human rights violations. Gaining experience in social work and communal aid, I aim to potentially work in a position that helps the community and increases my expertise in the field of human rights and education.
